Two men have been charged with stealing wreckage of the car in which Fast
& Furious actor Paul Walker died.

Jameson Witty, 18, and Anthony Janow, 25, were each charged on Monday with felony grand theft of personal
property and two misdemeanors - destroying evidence and resisting, obstructing
and delaying a peace officer.

If convicted, they both face up to four years and six months behind bars.

